---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";

const quizQuestions = [
  {
    question: "In what game does Mario work together with Bowser Jr. in order to save Bowser?",
    hint: "It's a DLC-pack.",
    answers: ["bowsers fury", "bowser's fury", "super mario 3d world bowsers fury", "super mario 3d world + bowsers fury"],
  },
  {
    question: "Which Mario game introduced Cappy as Mario's companion?",
    hint: "Think Nintendo Switch launch years.",
    answers: ["super mario odyssey", "mario odyssey"],
  },
  {
    question: "Who is the ruler of the Mushroom Kingdom?",
    hint: "She's often rescued by Mario.",
    answers: ["princess peach", "peach", "princess toadstool"],
  },
  {
    question: "What power-up makes Mario temporarily invincible?",
    hint: "It twinkles and plays a special theme.",
    answers: ["super star", "star", "starman", "invincibility star"],
  },
  {
    question: "Which console introduced the dual-screen setup used by many Mario handheld games?",
    hint: "A very popular Nintendo handheld from 2004.",
    answers: ["nintendo ds", "ds"],
  },
];
---

<MainLayout
  title="Home — The Great Mushroom Kingdom Wiki"
  description="Welcome to The Great Mushroom Kingdom Wiki! Here you'll find everything you need to know about the Mario universe."
  ogtitle="The Great Mushroom Kingdom Wiki"
  ogdescription="Welcome to The Great Mushroom Kingdom Wiki! Here you'll find everything you need to know about the Mario universe."
>
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-14 flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center gap-10 fade-in-up">
    <div class="flex-1">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold text-[#E52521] mb-6 leading-tight">Welcome!</h1>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Here on the great Mushroom Kingdom wiki, you'll find almost all things Mario and consoles. Go to the <a
          href="/universe"
          class="text-[#E52521] font-semibold underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-[#B81C19] interactive-link">Universe</a
        > menu to find the different wiki pages or the
        <a href="/about" class="text-[#E52521] font-semibold underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-[#B81C19] interactive-link">Information</a> page to
        learn more about the website!
      </p>
      <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
        For over 40 years, Mario has been a cultural icon in the gaming world. From humble arcade beginnings to exploring sprawling 3D kingdoms, the
        plumber has evolved and adapted across countless adventures. Whether you're here to dive deeper into specific games, characters, or consoles,
        you'll find everything you need to explore the Mushroom Kingdom.
      </p>
      <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        This wiki celebrates the franchise in all its forms— from the classic pixel-art era to modern masterpieces. Discover the power-ups that have
        saved the day, the villains that have caused chaos, and the consoles that brought these adventures to life.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="flex-1 flex justify-center">
      <img
        src="/images/front-image.webp"
        alt="Graffiti-art of Mario holding an NES controller"
        class="rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 shadow-lg w-full max-w-xs md:max-w-sm max-h-96 object-contain interactive-lift"
      />
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Consoles that shaped Mario Section -->
  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-14 fade-in-up-delayed">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-[#E52521] mb-3">Consoles that shaped Mario</h2>
    <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-8">A quick look at the Nintendo systems that helped define different eras of Mario games.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-10 items-start">
      <div class="flex-1">
        <img
          src="/images/switch3.webp"
          alt="Nintendo Switch gameplay"
          class="rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 shadow-md w-full max-h-72 object-cover mb-6 interactive-lift"
        />
        <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
          The Nintendo Switch brought Mario back into the mainstream in spectacular fashion. The console launched in 2017 with The Legend of Zelda:
          Breath of the Wild, but it was Super Mario Odyssey that truly captured the magic of the hybrid console. With its innovative motion controls
          and creative possession mechanic, Odyssey showed that Mario games could still surprise and delight after all these years.
        </p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          Since then, the Switch has been home to an incredible lineup of Mario titles. From 2D platformers like Super Mario Maker 2 to the whimsical
          Super Mario Bros. Wonder, the console has proven itself as the perfect platform for Mario's continued evolution. Whether docked, tabletop,
          or handheld, Mario feels right at home on the Switch.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="flex-1">
        <img
          src="/images/nintendo_ds.webp"
          alt="Nintendo DS console"
          class="rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 shadow-md w-full max-h-72 object-cover mb-6 interactive-lift"
        />
        <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
          But the Switch isn't the only console that matters in the Mario legacy. The Nintendo DS revolutionized portable gaming with its dual screens
          and touch input, giving us gems like New Super Mario Bros. and Mario Kart DS. Before that, the Wii brought motion controls into millions of
          living rooms with titles like Super Mario Galaxy and New Super Mario Bros. Wii.
        </p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-3">
          Each generation of consoles has brought new ways to experience Mario. These platforms represent not just technological evolution, but also
          the creative spirit that has kept the franchise fresh and exciting. From the couch-based experiences of home consoles to the
          pick-up-and-play nature of handheld systems, Mario has always found a way to be where players are.
        </p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
          That's why this wiki celebrates not just the games themselves, but also the hardware that made them possible. Because understanding Mario
          means understanding the consoles that brought him to life.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Quiz Section -->
  <section class="no-content-surface bg-[#049CD8] text-white py-12 fade-in-up">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-extrabold mb-4">The great Mario-quiz!</h2>
      <p id="quiz-question" class="mb-2 text-base leading-relaxed">
        {quizQuestions[0].question}
      </p>
      <p id="quiz-hint" class="mb-4 opacity-80 text-sm">
        Hint: {quizQuestions[0].hint}
      </p>
      <p id="quiz-feedback" class="hidden mb-4 text-sm font-semibold" aria-live="polite"></p>
      <form id="mario-quiz-form" class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-3 justify-center items-center">
        <label for="quiz-answer" class="sr-only">Your quiz answer</label>
        <input
          id="quiz-answer"
          name="quiz-answer"
          type="text"
          placeholder="Your answer..."
          class="rounded-[10px] px-5 py-2 text-mario-dark text-sm w-full sm:w-72 outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-[#FBD000]"
          required
        />
        <button
          id="quiz-submit"
          type="submit"
          class="bg-[#FBD000] text-mario-dark font-bold px-6 py-2 rounded-[10px] hover:brightness-110 transition-all interactive-lift"
        >
          Submit
        </button>
        <button
          id="quiz-next"
          type="button"
          class="bg-white/20 text-white font-bold px-6 py-2 rounded-[10px] hover:bg-white/30 transition-all interactive-lift"
        >
          Next question
        </button>
      </form>
    </div>
  </section>

  <script is:inline define:vars={{ quizQuestions }}>
    const form = document.getElementById("mario-quiz-form");
    const questionEl = document.getElementById("quiz-question");
    const hintEl = document.getElementById("quiz-hint");
    const feedbackEl = document.getElementById("quiz-feedback");
    const answerInput = document.getElementById("quiz-answer");
    const nextButton = document.getElementById("quiz-next");

    let currentIndex = 0;

    const normalizeAnswer = (value) =>
      value
        .toLowerCase()
        .normalize("NFD")
        .replace(/[\u0300-\u036f]/g, "")
        .replace(/[^a-z0-9\s]/g, "")
        .replace(/\s+/g, " ")
        .trim();

    const setQuestion = (index) => {
      currentIndex = index;
      const item = quizQuestions[currentIndex];
      questionEl.textContent = item.question;
      hintEl.textContent = `Hint: ${item.hint}`;
      feedbackEl.textContent = "";
      feedbackEl.classList.add("hidden");
      feedbackEl.classList.remove("text-[#FBD000]", "text-[#ffd6d6]");
      answerInput.value = "";
      answerInput.focus();
    };

    const randomNextIndex = () => {
      if (quizQuestions.length < 2) return currentIndex;
      let next = currentIndex;
      while (next === currentIndex) {
        next = Math.floor(Math.random() * quizQuestions.length);
      }
      return next;
    };

    form?.addEventListener("submit", (event) => {
      event.preventDefault();
      const currentQuestion = quizQuestions[currentIndex];
      const userAnswer = normalizeAnswer(answerInput.value);

      if (!userAnswer) {
        feedbackEl.classList.remove("hidden");
        feedbackEl.textContent = "Please type an answer first.";
        feedbackEl.classList.remove("text-[#FBD000]");
        feedbackEl.classList.add("text-[#ffd6d6]");
        return;
      }

      const isCorrect = currentQuestion.answers.some((accepted) => normalizeAnswer(accepted) === userAnswer);

      if (isCorrect) {
        feedbackEl.classList.remove("hidden");
        feedbackEl.textContent = "Correct! Nice one 🍄";
        feedbackEl.classList.remove("text-[#ffd6d6]");
        feedbackEl.classList.add("text-[#FBD000]");
        window.setTimeout(() => setQuestion(randomNextIndex()), 900);
        return;
      }

      feedbackEl.classList.remove("hidden");
      feedbackEl.textContent = "Not quite—try again or jump to a new question.";
      feedbackEl.classList.remove("text-[#FBD000]");
      feedbackEl.classList.add("text-[#ffd6d6]");
    });

    nextButton?.addEventListener("click", () => {
      setQuestion(randomNextIndex());
    });
  </script>

  <!-- Did You Know Section -->
  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-14 flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center gap-10 fade-in-up-delayed">
    <div class="flex-1">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-[#E52521] mb-5">Did you know that...</h2>
      <p class="text-base text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        The first "non-official" Mario game, <strong>Mario Bros.</strong>, was released back in 1983 as an arcade game? While the Super Mario Bros.
        game from 1985 is seen as the first official game in the franchise, many forget that this 43-year-old hidden gem is the one that kickstarted
        the series for good.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="flex-1 flex justify-center">
      <div class="rounded-[1.75rem] p-4 w-full max-w-[18rem] md:max-w-[20rem] interactive-lift">
        <img
          src="/images/mario-retro.webp"
          alt="Picture of old Mario game"
          class="rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 w-full max-h-80 object-contain"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</MainLayout>
